@startuml Identity and API Integration Patterns

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 10
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Identity & API Integration Patterns for Cross-Tenant Agents

== Pattern 1: Delegated User Access (OBO Flow) ==

actor "Corporate User" as user1
participant "M365 Copilot" as copilot1
participant "Corporate Agent" as agent1
participant "Enterprise\nEntra ID" as entra1
participant "Retail\nEntra ID" as entra2
participant "Retail API" as api1

user1 -> copilot1: Invoke agent
copilot1 -> entra1: Authenticate user
entra1 --> copilot1: Access token (user)
copilot1 -> agent1: Execute with user token
agent1 -> entra1: OBO token exchange\n(for Retail API scope)
entra1 -> entra2: Cross-tenant token\n(B2B trust)
entra2 --> agent1: Downstream token
agent1 -> api1: Call API with\ndownstream token
api1 --> agent1: Response
agent1 --> copilot1: Agent response
copilot1 --> user1: Display result

note over entra1, entra2
  Requires:
  - Cross-tenant access settings
  - B2B collaboration enabled
  - API permissions consented
end note

== Pattern 2: Application-Only Access (Client Credentials) ==

participant "Scheduled Job" as job
participant "Corporate Agent" as agent2
participant "Enterprise\nEntra ID" as entra3
participant "Retail\nEntra ID" as entra4
participant "Retail API" as api2

job -> agent2: Trigger scheduled task
agent2 -> entra3: Client credentials\n(certificate)
entra3 --> agent2: App-only token
agent2 -> api2: Call API\n(multi-tenant app)
note right: Service principal\nexists in Retail\ntenant via consent
api2 -> entra4: Validate token
entra4 --> api2: Token valid
api2 --> agent2: Response
agent2 --> job: Task complete

note over entra3, entra4
  Requires:
  - Multi-tenant app registration
  - Admin consent in Retail tenant
  - Certificate-based auth (no secrets)
end note

== Pattern 3: Workload Identity Federation ==

participant "Azure Function\n(Agent Host)" as func
participant "User-Assigned\nManaged Identity" as mi
participant "Enterprise\nEntra ID" as entra5
participant "Retail\nEntra ID" as entra6
participant "Retail API" as api3

func -> mi: Request token
mi -> entra5: Federated credential\n(no secrets)
entra5 --> mi: Token for\nmulti-tenant app
mi --> func: Access token
func -> api3: Call Retail API
api3 -> entra6: Validate token
entra6 --> api3: Token valid
api3 --> func: Response

note over mi
  Benefits:
  - No secrets to manage
  - Auto-rotation
  - Audit trail
end note

@enduml
